'''Diana Slip''' was an early 20th-century French manufacturer of [[lingerie]] and [[fetishwear]], founded by Léon Vidal, the publisher of [[Les Éditions Gauloises]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.anothermag.com/fashion-beauty/8761/the-forgotten-fetishwear-company-of-twenties-paris|title=The Forgotten Fetishwear Company of 1920s Paris|last=Singer|first=Olivia|date=|work=|newspaper=AnOther|access-date=2016-10-12|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://flashbak.com/vintage-bondage-and-fetish-gear-by-yva-richard-and-diana-slip-nsfw-361517/|title=Vintage Bondage and Fetish Gear By Yva Richard and Diana Slip (NSFW) {{!}}|last=Strike|first=Karen|date=|work=|newspaper=Flashbak|access-date=2016-10-12|via=}}</ref>  They employed renowned photographers of the time, including [[Roger Schall]] and [[Brassaï]], to photograph their products.<ref name=":0" /> 
Their main competitor was [[Yva Richard]].<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite book|title=Yva Richard : L'âge d'or du fétichisme|last=Dupouy|first=Alexandre|publisher=Editions Astarté|year=1994|isbn=978-2909607030|language=French|quote=|via=}}</ref>

