{{redirect|Lifeworks|the American consulting company in the early 1990s|Richard Thieme}} {{infobox company |name = GoBeyond Student Travel |logo = [[File:GoBeyond_Logo.jpg|frameless]] |type = [[Private company|Private]] |website = https://www.gobeyondtravel.com |founded = 2003 |founders = {{unbulleted list | Jim Stoll | Mike Meighan}} |former_name = Lifeworks International |hq_location_city = [[Sarasota, Florida]] |hq_location_country = United States |area_served = Worldwide |industry = Service Learning Organization |parent = [[Global Expeditions Group]]
}}
'''GoBeyond Student Travel''' is an organization which offers [[community service]] based adventure programs during the Northern Hemisphere summertime to teenagers. Programs are run in the [[British Virgin Islands]], [[Ecuador]] and the [[Galapagos]], [[Thailand]], [[China]], [[Costa Rica]], [[India]], [[Peru]] and [[Australia]].
== History == GoBeyond grew from the experience of its sister institutions, [[ActionQuest]] and [[Seamester|Sea|mester]], with a decided aim on global [[community service]]. After the events of September 11, 2001, [[ActionQuest]] decided to develop a program aimed at service, which became GoBeyond Student Travel.<ref name="C. L.">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2008/04/18/ST2008041802138.html |title=Teens on a Mission: What a Trip |publisher=Washington Post |accessdate=2005-09-17 | first=Cindy | last=Loose}}</ref>
GoBeyond ran its first programs in 2003 in the [[British Virgin Islands]], [[Australia]], and the [[Galapagos]]. In 2004, GoBeyond [[Thailand]] began, and in 2005, GoBeyond [[China]] and [[Costa Rica]] began.<ref name=C.L.>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/04/18/AR2008041800947.html |title=Exotic Expeditions: Make Bricks in Peru, Renovate an Indonesian Temple |publisher=Washington Post |accessdate=2005-09-17}}</ref> In 2010, GoBeyond expanded offerings to India and Peru.
