{{Infobox journal | title = International Journal of Public Opinion Research | cover = International Journal of Public Opinion Research.gif | editor = Paul Brewer, Michael Xenos | discipline = | language = [[English language|English]] | abbreviation = Int. J. Public Opin. Res. | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | country = [[United Kingdom]] | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1989 to present | impact = 1.644 | impact-year = 2016 | website = http://ijpor.oxfordjournals.org/ | ISSN = 0954-2892 | eISSN = 1471-6909 }}
The '''''International Journal of Public Opinion Research''''' ('''''IJPOR''''') is a quarterly [[social sciences|social science]] [[academic journal|journal]] sponsored by the [[World Association for Public Opinion Research]] (WAPOR) and published by [[Oxford University Press]].<ref> {{cite web | url = http://ijpor.oxfordjournals.org/ | title = Oxford Journals: Social Sciences – Int. Journal of Public Opinion Research | accessdate = 2007-12-28 | year = 2007 | publisher = [[Oxford Journals]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.unl.edu/wapor/membership_info.html |title = World Association for Public Opinion Research |accessdate = 2007-12-28 |publisher = [[World Association for Public Opinion Research]] |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080102024441/http://www.unl.edu/WAPOR/membership_info.html |archive-date = 2008-01-02 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref>
Since 1994, WAPOR bestows the [[Robert Worcester|Robert M. Worcester]] Prize for "outstanding" publication in ''IJPOR'';<ref> {{cite web |url = http://www.unl.edu/WAPOR/awards.html |title = Awards and Prizes |accessdate = 2007-12-28 |publisher = [[World Association for Public Opinion Research]] |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080102024431/http://www.unl.edu/WAPOR/awards.html |archivedate = 2008-01-02 |df = }}</ref> among prior recipients of the prize is communications researcher [[Dietram Scheufele]].<ref> {{cite web |url = http://www.unl.edu/WAPOR/award%20winners.htm |title = Award Winners |accessdate = 2007-12-28 |publisher = [[World Association for Public Opinion Research]] |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071203184335/http://www.unl.edu/wapor/award%20winners.htm |archivedate = 2007-12-03 |df = }}</ref>
